Deladriendil now shoots arrows doing base damage of 44 /35 at 420 Range.  420 range.  That is well out of the aggro range of all but some boss mobs.  hell most mobs can't find you when you aggro them from that far.<br>
<br>
that 44/35 base damage is modified with an occasional extra 4 points of Raw damage from 4 fire - this is similar to main hand damage bonus.  it is not added to the base damage hense not multiplied - in essence it is just a potential extra 4 points of damage.<br>
<br>
consider that a 44 damage weapon can often hit over 300 points of damage non crit.  Now consider that every mob that is hit by an arrow shot by a 51 and over ranger- while the mob is not rooted or moving is hit for double damage.<br>
<br>
thats in the 600 range. now consider that when a ranger dises trueshot he is going to do some quad shots - that is a max of 1200ish.<br>
<br>
With Archery mastery, that can double.  up  to around 2400 damage per shot for 2 minutes.  consider this ranger has inate quiver haste( don't know if EQ quiver haste is the same as Fleeting or not) plus is hasted by worn haste plus spell haste.  Note - that both of our EQ rangers have the capabilty to self haste to aroun 80% haste  plus quiver haste.<br>
<br>
I don't know the math = but that is a lot of damage in 2 minutes.  At this point arks damage is only slightly less while using his BFT.<br>
<br>
Bottom line - both these guys at a raid can seriously make an encounter with a 200kHP to 500kHP mob - errr better.<br>
<br>
Tanks - keep that boss mob out of a wall if possible.<br>
<br>
